  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, EnricherListener<P>, EntityEnricherListener<P>, ParticipantEnricherListener<P>, AliasesChangeListener<P>, AnnotationsChangeListener<P>, EntityChangeListener<P>, EntityInteractorChangeListener, ParticipantChangeListener<P>, XrefsChangeListener<P>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParticipantEvidenceEnricherListenerManager, ParticipantPoolEnricherListenerManager
    public class ParticipantEnricherListenerManager<P extends Participant>
extends EntityEnricherListenerManager<P>
implements ParticipantEnricherListener<P>
    A manager for listeners which holds a list of listeners. Listener manager allows enrichers to send events to multiple listeners. A listener itself, it implements all methods which will then fire the corresponding method in each entry of the listener list. No promise can be given to the order in which the listeners are fired.
    Since:
    10/07/13
    Author:
    Gabriel Aldam (galdam@ebi.ac.uk)
